headline: KKR, Warburg Pincus Among Suitors for Southeast Asia School Operator
summary: Private-equity firms KKR and Warburg Pincus are among the bidders vying to acquire TPG’s Southeast Asia school business, which could be valued at up to $2 billion, people familiar with the process said.
